<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-628-323  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 628 323.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 14 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Geography-based games/education for IBM, Apple. (from PC GlobeInc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zucker, Paul.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   PC Globe Inc. (Marketing).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersMarketing StrategyComputer gamesGeographyEducational Games.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>GEOGRAPHY-BASED GAMES/EDUCATION FOR IBM, APPLE 11/14/90 LAS VEGAS, NEVADA,U.S.A., 1990 NOV 14 (NB) -- PC Globe Inc. is known for its educational andreference products based on geography themes -- it now has games based on thesame theme.andP;  BushBuck Charms, Viking Ships andamp; Dodo Eggs (hereafter calledBCVSDE for obvious reasons) is a PC product with similarities to the &quot;Wherein the .... Carmen Sandiego&quot; series.andM;BCVSDE teaches geography, world history, and social studies to users of allages by setting scavenger-hunt challenges, either against a computerizedopponent or a live one.andP;  GeoJigsaw and Geopuzzle USA, for the Apple family,are expected to be popular with school students and teachers alike.andM;The company's mainstay products are the acclaimed PC Globe and PC USA, now inversions 4.0 and 2.0 respectively.andP;  These allow users to examine the globe,looking at and geographic, economic, political and other aspects of countriesor regions, right down to city level.andP;  You can hear a national anthem,compare meat production between Australia and Austria, or plot populationestimates into the next century.andM;(Paul Zucker/19901114/Contact: PC Globe Inc. 602-7309000)</TEXT></DOC>